{
  "stem": "25639.9",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the doctor said, she'll be all right, that she-- she just needs to be rehabilitated but that she will be all right.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "How did they know about you?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, they just saw me on a bicycle riding around the schoolyard.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this was so wonderful.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I did it for fun because I had to use a bicycle in the summer to go to school, and spring and whenever the weather permitting.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Otherwise, I had to take the train in the winter time.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That was back home, of course.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and they started sending me Swedish letters, and I couldn't read them but some of the nurses translated it to German, and so, slowly, I-- I could understand it.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And with the help of the inmates, we answered in German to the Swedish family, and eventually, they asked me if I would like to become a daughter-- a sister to their daughter, Gulan.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That's her name, Gulan.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "She was one year younger than I, and it was so nice for me to meet someone close to my age, who had a so-called normal life.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Eventually, when they asked me to become their daughter, I wrote to them that [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I am in a state of mind still that I believe that perhaps some of my family have survived.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I don't want to be adopted, but I would love to come and live with them.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And once the Swedish Red Cross permitted me to be released, I could go and live with them.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But after quarantine, we-- we went to another-- we were sent to another camp for rehabilitation.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We were continually under doctor-- doctor's care.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I was the youngest member of that transport, by the way, to Sweden.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
